<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Memorandum by Lieutenant General Alvan
                            C. Gillem, Jr., to General Marshall</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d119</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">119</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by Lieutenant General <persName type="from">Alvan
                            C. Gillem, Jr.</persName>, to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-24">24 April
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In response to your request as to the method of settlement for equipment for
                    Communist Training, “War 82174” states that “Equipment transferred for Communist
                    Training will be under straight <pb facs="0350" n="338" xml:id="pg_338"/>
                        Lend-Lease.”<note n="55" xml:id="d119fn55">Not found in Department files; it
                        was received at the Shanghai headquarters of the U. S. Army in China on
                        March 29.</note> Inquiries have been made regarding where to store Communist
                    Divisional equipment until needed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A. C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Gillem, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
